# Tailwind CSS Usage Rules

All styling must be done through Tailwind CSS classes and configuration, not inline styles or CSS-in-JS.

## Core Principles

1. **No inline styles** - Never use `style={{}}` prop in React components
2. **No CSS-in-JS** - Do not use styled-components, emotion, or similar libraries
3. **Use Tailwind classes** - All styling should use Tailwind utility classes via `className`
4. **Extend @theme block** - Custom colors, animations, and utilities go in the `@theme` block in `index.css`
5. **Custom utilities via @utility** - Reusable component patterns go in `index.css` using `@utility` directives

## Font System

- **Body text**: Uses `IBM Plex Mono` via `--font-sans` (Tailwind default body font)
- **Headings (h1-h6)**: Uses `Inter` via `--font-heading` (applied automatically in base styles)
- Apply `font-heading` class to override individual elements to use Inter
- Never load fonts via CSS `@import` — use `<link>` tags in `index.html`

## Color System

- **Primary orange**: `#FF570A` — use `text-primary`, `bg-primary`, `border-primary` etc.
- **DO NOT** use hardcoded Tailwind palette colors like `text-orange-600`, `bg-orange-500`
- Use design tokens: `text-primary`, `bg-primary/10`, `border-primary/20`, `hover:text-primary`
- Gradients use `bg-gradient-button`, `bg-gradient-title`, `bg-gradient-auth` tokens

## Allowed Approaches

### ✅ Use Tailwind Utility Classes

```tsx
// ✅ Correct - Using Tailwind classes
<div className="flex items-center justify-center min-h-screen bg-background">
  <Card className="w-full max-w-md p-6">
    <h1 className="text-2xl font-bold text-foreground">Title</h1>
  </Card>
</div>
```

### ✅ Extend @theme Block (Tailwind v4)

**`index.css`**:
```css
@theme {
  --font-sans: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;
  --font-heading: 'Inter', sans-serif;

  --color-primary: hsl(var(--primary));
  --color-primary-foreground: hsl(var(--primary-foreground));

  --background-image-gradient-button: linear-gradient(
    to right,
    rgb(255 87 10),
    rgb(220 80 20)
  );
}
```

**Component**:
```tsx
// ✅ Correct - Using custom Tailwind utilities from @theme
<button className="bg-gradient-button hover:bg-gradient-button-hover text-white">
  Click me
</button>
```

### ✅ Use Custom Utilities in CSS

**`index.css`**:
```css
@utility btn-primary {
  @apply bg-gradient-button hover:bg-gradient-button-hover text-white font-medium px-6 py-2 rounded-md transition-all duration-200;
}

@utility card-unified {
  @apply bg-card border border-border rounded-lg shadow-xs;
}

@utility btn-card {
  @apply w-full flex items-center gap-4 bg-card border border-border rounded-md px-6 py-4 text-foreground font-medium transition-colors hover:border-primary/50 hover:bg-primary/5 cursor-pointer;
}
```

**Component**:
```tsx
// ✅ Correct - Using component classes from CSS
<button className="btn-primary">Click me</button>
<Card className="card-unified">Content</Card>
<button className="btn-card">
  <Icon /> Select option
</button>
```

## Prohibited Approaches

### ❌ Inline Styles

```tsx
// ❌ Incorrect - Using inline styles
<div style={{ display: "flex", alignItems: "center", padding: "1rem" }}>
  Content
</div>

// ✅ Correct - Use Tailwind classes
<div className="flex items-center p-4">
  Content
</div>
```

### ❌ CSS-in-JS Libraries

```tsx
// ❌ Incorrect - Using styled-components or emotion
const StyledButton = styled.button`
  background: linear-gradient(to right, #c2410c, #b91c1c);
  padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
`;

// ✅ Correct - Use Tailwind classes or component classes
<button className="bg-gradient-button px-4 py-2">Click me</button>
```

### ❌ Hardcoded Tailwind Palette Colors

```tsx
// ❌ Incorrect - Using hardcoded orange/red colors
<span className="text-orange-600">Text</span>
<div className="bg-orange-100">Background</div>
<button className="bg-linear-to-r from-orange-500 to-red-500">Button</button>

// ✅ Correct - Use design tokens
<span className="text-primary">Text</span>
<div className="bg-primary/10">Background</div>
<button className="bg-gradient-button">Button</button>
```

## Button Styling

- **Primary action buttons (CTAs) MUST use the gradient button classes:**
  - Use `bg-gradient-button hover:bg-gradient-button-hover text-white` for all primary action buttons
  - Or use the `btn-primary` / `btn-primary-large` utility classes
  - This applies to submit buttons, save buttons, create buttons, and any other primary CTAs
  - **DO NOT** use hardcoded colors like `bg-orange-500 hover:bg-orange-600`

- **Card-style selection buttons MUST use `btn-card`:**
  - Use for provider selectors, option cards, and selection-style buttons
  - White/card background with thin border, hover highlight

## Toggle Input Styling

- **Switch/Toggle components MUST use the gradient button classes when checked:**
  - Use `data-[state=checked]:bg-gradient-button` for all Switch components
  - This ensures toggle switches match the design system's gradient styling
  - **DO NOT** rely on default `bg-primary` styling for switches

## File Organization

- **`index.css` @theme block** - Custom theme extensions (colors, fonts, gradients, animations)
- **`index.css` @utility blocks** - Reusable component utilities (btn-primary, card-unified, etc.)
- **`index.css` @layer base** - CSS variables, base styles, heading font rules
- **`styles/*.css`** - Third-party component overrides only (e.g., `google-auth.css`)

## Cross-App Consistency

All 3 apps (`web`, `app`, `portal`) MUST share identical:
- Font tokens (`--font-sans`, `--font-heading`)
- Color variables (`:root` and `.dark` blocks)
- Gradient definitions (`gradient-button`, `gradient-title`, `gradient-auth`)
- Core utility definitions (`btn-primary`, `card-unified`, `btn-card`, `title-gradient`, etc.)

Portal-specific utilities (`billing-toggle`, `license-card-*`, `icon-*`) only exist in portal's CSS.
